<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Containing block for absolute positioned elements is nearest positioned (fixed) ancestor.</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If the element has 'position: absolute', the containing block is established by the nearest positioned ancestor." />
        <style>
            #d1
            {
                margin: 50px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                position: fixed;
                height: 23px;
                width: 360px;
                top: 20px;
                left: 20px;
                border: solid green 2px;
            }
            #d3
            {
                height: 10px;
                width: 10px;
                float: right;
            }
            #d4
            {
                position: absolute;
                width: 100%;
                top: 2px;
                left: 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2">
                <div id="d3">
                    <div id="d4">Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>Test passes if the "Filler Text" is contained within the green box.</p>
    </body>
</html>